9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1224, L.D. 1829, “An Act to Build
10 Housing for Maine Families and Attract Workers to Maine Businesses by Amending the
11 Laws Governing Municipal Land Use Decisions”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Build Housing for Maine Families and Attract Workers to Maine
14 Businesses by Amending the Laws Governing Housing Density'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2463-B is enacted to read:
18 §2463-B. Fire protection in accessory dwelling units
19 Fire suppression sprinklers are not required for an accessory dwelling unit unless the
20 accessory dwelling unit is within or attached to a structure of more than 2 dwelling units,
21 including accessory dwelling units. As used in this section, "accessory dwelling unit" has
22 the same meaning as in Title 30-A, section 4301, subsection 1-C.
23 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§1-C, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 145, §1 and
24 reallocated by RR 2019, c. 1, Pt. A, §36, is amended to read:
25 1-C. Accessory dwelling unit. "Accessory dwelling unit" means a self‑contained
26 dwelling unit located within, attached to or detached from a single-family dwelling unit or
27 multi-unit structure located on the same parcel of land.
28 Sec. 3. 30-A MRSA §4360, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2003, c. 127, §1, is amended
29 to read:
30 2. Differential ordinances. A municipality may enact rate of growth ordinances that
31 set different limits on the number of building or development permits that are permitted in
32 designated rural areas and designated growth areas. A municipality may not enact rate of
33 growth ordinances that limit residential development in designated growth areas, as defined
34 in section 4301, subsection 6-C, except as authorized by this chapter.
